ft_scanf:
Allowed functions: fgetc, ungetc, ferror, isspace, isdigit, stdin, va_start_, va_arg ...
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a function  named `ft_scanf` that will mimic the real scanf
- Manage conversions only: s d and c
- You don't have to handle the maximum field width
- You don't have to handle the type modifier characters

Your function must be declared :
int ft_scanf(const char *, ...)
